3.00	For_Lovers_Only	For Lovers Only	For Lovers Only is a 1995 covers/pop standards album by The Temptations for the Motown label, something of a sequel to their 1967 album The Temptations in a Mellow Mood. The album features the final recordings of Melvin Franklin, who fell ill during recording and died before the album's release. Franklin was replaced on the tracks he does not sing on by P-Funk's Ray Davis.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/11/Tempts-forloversonly.jpg/220px-Tempts-forloversonly.jpg
